          <b><span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">νηλεής, νηλής</span></b>  (<span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">νη-, ἔλεος</span>): <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">pitiless, ruthless,
            relentless;</span> of persons, and often fig., <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">θῡμός, ἦτορ, δεσμός, νηλεὲς ἦμαρ</span>, ‘day of
          death’; <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ὕπνος</span>, of a sleep productive
          of disastrous consequences, <i><span class="en">Od.
            12.372</span></i>.</div> <div class="alpheios-lex-footnotes en"> </div>
